15,01Words of Wisdom 
15,01---------------------

15,01All things being equal, fat people use more soap. 

15,01Anything worth fighting for is worth fighting dirty for. 

15,01By the time you make ends meet, they move the ends. 

15,01Everything should be made as simple as possible, but no simpler. 

15,01Friends may come and go, but enemies accumulate. 

15,01Happiness is merely the remission of pain. 

15,01I have seen the truth and it makes no sense. 

15,01If you can smile when things go wrong, you have someone in mind to blame. 

15,01If you think there is good in everybody, you haven't met everybody. 

15,01Indecision is the key to flexibility. 

15,01Never wrestle a pig. You both get dirty, and the pig likes it. 

15,01Not one shred of evidence supports the notion that life is serious. 

15,01One seventh of your life is spent on Monday. 

15,01Someone who thinks logically is a nice contrast to the real world. 

15,01Sometimes too much to drink is not enough. 

15,01Suicide is the most sincere form of self-criticism. 

15,01The careful application of terror is also a form of communication. 

15,01The facts, although interesting, are irrelevant. 

15,01The more you run over a cat, the flatter it gets. 

15,01There is absolutely no substitute for a genuine lack of preparation. 

15,01There is always one more imbecile than you counted on. 

15,01Things are more like they are today than they ever were before.
